### Login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "admin@mail.com",
    "password": "power@123"
}

### Check auth user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

{
    "with": ["name", "email", "permissions"]
}

# Customers API

# Manage customer records. The customers table contains the following notable columns:
# - `businessName`: the primary name of the company
# - `status`: one of 'active', 'standby', 'archived', 'inactive'

## Endpoints

### List Customers (Paginated)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/customers?page=1&per_page=10&search=Acme
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

### List All Customers (Short)
# Returns an unpaginated list of all customers, primarily for use in dropdowns.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/customers/all
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

### List All Customers full data (paginated)
# Returns a paginated list of customers, with full data.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/customers?page=1&per_page=5
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

### Get Customer
# Retrieve a single customer.
GET http://localhost:3000/api/customers/1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

### Create Customer
# Creates a new customer.
POST http://localhost:3000/api/customers
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

{
  "businessName": "New Corp",
  "nameOnInvoice": "New Corp Ltd",
  "status": "active",
  "email": "contact@newcorp.com"
}

### Update Customer
# Updates an existing customer.
# PUT `/api/customers/:id`

PUT http://localhost:3000/api/customers/1
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

### Get Next Invoice Number
# Returns the next sequential invoice number for this customer.

# **GET** `/api/customers/:id/invoices/next-number`

GET http://localhost:3000/api/customers/1/invoices/next-number
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}


# Invoices API

# Manage customer invoices with automatic calculations for subtotals, discounts, and totals.

## Endpoints

### List Invoices (Paginated)
# Retrieves a paginated list of invoices.

# **GET** `/api/invoices`
GET http://localhost:3000/api/invoices?page=1&per_page=10&status=sent
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}


### Get Invoice
# Retrieve a single invoice and its items. Can join with the customer name.
# **GET** `/api/invoices/:id`
GET http://localhost:3000/api/invoices/1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

### Create Invoice
# Creates a new invoice for a customer. The backend automatically calculates `discount_amount`, `subtotal`, and `total`.
# **POST** `/api/invoices`

POST http://localhost:3000/api/invoices
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

{
  "customerId": 1,
  "number": 2,
  "currency": "USD",
  "status": "draft",
  "items": [
    {
      "name": "Service A",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unit_price": 500
    }
  ],
  "discountType": "percent",
  "discountValue": 10,
  "fees": []
}

### Update Invoice
# Updates an invoice, recalculating totals automatically on save.
#
# **PUT** `/api/invoices/:id`

PUT http://localhost:3000/api/invoices/1
Accept: application/json
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{AUTH_TOKEN}}

{
  "status": "sent",
  "items": [
    {
      "name": "Service A",
      "quantity": 3,
      "unit_price": 500
    }
  ]
}
